\layout Section

What is Umix ?
\layout Standard

Umix is a program for adjusting soundcard mixers in Linux and other Unices.
 You can control your volumes, balances and recording sources flexibly from
 the command line, or with a fullscreen user interface.
 Umix currently supports Linux, OSS and dummy mixer devices.
 I designed it as an replacement for Aumix.
\layout Subsection

How to use Umix ?
\layout Standard

Read the man-page.
\layout Subsection

What does Umix mean ?
\layout Standard

Nothing particular.
 Ultimate Mixer ? Unix Mixer ? Something like that.
 Yes, I know it's a dull name.
\layout Subsection

Why another volume mixer ?
\layout Standard

I got frustrated with Aumix, and there were no other good alternatives that
 had terminal/ncurses user interfaces.
 I myself like to do all my work in a console, and at the same time I usually
 listen to mp3/nsf music, and need to adjust my soundcard volumes constantly.
 Aumix acts weird, eats too much CPU cycles etc.
 If you want to modify it in any sensible way, total rewrite would be the
 only way.
